 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Research Plant Physiologist/Agronomist US Agricultural Research Service Stoneville, MS Job details Salary $77,488 - $119,787 a year Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Duties 
 Summary 
 Incumbent is a Research Agronomist/Research Plant Physiologist at the United States Department of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service in the Crop Production Systems Research Unit (CPSRU), Stoneville, MS. As a research scientist, the incumbent has full responsibility for initiating, developing and managing independent research projects, addressing mainly corn, soybean, and other crops grown in rotation, and alternative crops production systems. 
 
 Responsibilities 
 Improve production practices to enhance productivity, profitability, water and energy use efficiency, and natural resources conservation for crop production in the lower Mississippi River valley. 
 Reduce the need for water and chemical inputs and reduce production costs and risks. 
 Develop economical production practices for new genetically modified organism (GMO) and stacked-gene corn hybrids. 
 Apply Artificial Intelligence in combining advanced technologies such as precision agriculture (site-specific management, automation, remote sensing, etc.,) in developing crop production practices that decrease water and energy inputs. 
 Determine the role of specific crops, including cover crops in carbon cycling, develop ways to quantify carbon outputs, and estimate its potential profitability to producers. 
 Travel Required 
 Occasional travel - You may be expected to travel for this position. 
